  <evidence rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string">Internet Log Files The Company may also keep track of IP addresses used to access its Online Services for various reasons An IP address is a number that is used by a networked device and will identify your point of connection to the internet Depending on your network configuration it may also identify your computer or other device A MAC address or other device ID identifies one specific piece of hardware These log files are tied to your personal information in certain circumstances such as if you have linked your console user account to Online Service accounts offered by the Company</evidence>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

